addStrategy(address).details: It is registered at which time the strategy has been added. Time must pass for the strategies to be able to request funds from the `LendingVault`.

approve(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-approve}. NOTE: If `amount` is the maximum `uint256`, the allowance is not updated on `transferFrom`. This is semantically equivalent to an infinite approval. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

decimals().details: Decimals are computed by adding the decimal offset on top of the underlying asset's decimals. This "original" value is cached during construction of the vault contract. If this read operation fails (e.g., the asset has not been created yet), a default of 18 is used to represent the underlying asset's decimals. See {IERC20Metadata-decimals}.

decreaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically decreases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller. This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address. - `spender` must have allowance for the caller of at least `subtractedValue`.

increaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically increases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller. This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

name().details: Returns the name of the token.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

params._strategy: The address of the strategy to remove.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

replenishAssets(uint256).details: Setting `totalAssetsAllocatedInStrategies` to 0, should be the same as doing `totalAssetsAllocatedInStrategies -= (_amount - potentialProfit)`.

symbol().details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

transfer(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transfer}. Requirements: - `to` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have a balance of at least `amount`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. This is not required by the EIP. See the note at the beginning of {ERC20}. NOTE: Does not update the allowance if the current allowance is the maximum `uint256`. Requirements: - `from` and `to` cannot be the zero address. - `from` must have a balance of at least `amount`. - the caller must have allowance for ``from``'s tokens of at least `amount`.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

addStrategy(address).notice: Way to add new strategies that allocate capital from the vault.

adjustPerformanceFee(uint16).notice: Adjusts the `performanceFee` of the `LendingVault`. The fee can range from 0-20%.

deposit(uint256,address).notice: To protect users, depositing is halted when the vault is paused.

incurredLosses().notice: This number will reflect losses from the underlying strategies.

mint(uint256,address).notice: To protect users, minting is halted when the vault is paused.

pause().notice: Pauses the vault to prevent further deposits/withdraw until it is safe.

performanceFeeRecipient().notice: The address where performance fees direct towards.

redeem(uint256,address,address).notice: In case of an emergency, `redeem` is halted temporarily.

removeStrategy(address).notice: Unauthorize a strategy. It essentially means it can no longer call `requestAssets`. Can still call `replenishAssets`.

replenishAssets(uint256).notice: This function is unrestricted and anyone can call it. It is assumed to be safe because the `asset` is trusted.

requestAssets(uint256).notice: Only strategies are able to call this function and request assets from the vault and a period of `DELAY_TO_REQUEST_ASSETS` needs to have transpired before they can request assets.

setPerformanceFeeRecipient(address).notice: Changes the recipient of the 20% performance fees.

unpause().notice: Unpauses the contract to enable deposits/withdraws to the vault.

withdraw(uint256,address,address).notice: In case of an emergency, `withdraw` is halted temporarily.

writeOffLosses(uint256).notice: We should be able to adjust the accounting in case the underlying protocols make bad loans or get hacked. This means all users get an equitative haircut in their assets to shares ratio.
